o\": 1099}, {\"ngram\": \"silver\", \"from\": 1104, \"to\": 1110}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"from\": 1161, \"to\": 1165}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100m breaststrokeon\", \"from\": 1169, \"to\": 1192}]}, {\"sentence\": \"She also became the country's most decorated Olympian of all time.\", \"from\": 1202, \"to\": 1268, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1250, \"end\": 1258, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"score\": 0.9999834380562775, \"rank\": 1.6562218171651716e-05, \"text\": \"Olympian\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Olympic_Games\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"all time\", \"from\": 1259, \"to\": 1267}]}, {\"sentence\": \"While she equalled the record haul of fellow swimmer Chad le Clos, she holds more gold medals.\", \"from\": 1269, \"to\": 1363, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1317, \"end\": 1324, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"score\": 0.9999999927690624, \"rank\": 7.2191066540923694e-09, \"text\": \"swimmer\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_Summer_Olympics\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Swimming_at_the_Summer_Olympics\"}, {\"begin\": 1325, \"end\": 1337, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Chad le Clos\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\", \"Q10843402\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Chad_le_Clos\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the record haul\", \"from\": 1288, \"to\": 1303}, {\"ngram\": \"more gold medals\", \"from\": 1346, \"to\": 1362}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Half an hour earlier,Pieter Coetzeswam the race of his life but finished well off the pace in the men's 200m backstroke final, settling for seventh position.\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1522, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Half an hour earlier,Pieter Coetzeswam\", \"from\": 1365, \"to\": 1403}, {\"ngram\": \"the race\", \"from\": 1404, \"to\": 1412}, {\"ngram\": \"his life\", \"from\": 1416, \"to\": 1424}, {\"ngram\": \"the pace\", \"from\": 1447, \"to\": 1455}, {\"ngram\": \"the men's 200m backstroke\", \"from\": 1459, \"to\": 1484}, {\"ngram\": \"seventh position\", \"from\": 1505, \"to\": 1521}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Coetze, who was fifth in the 100m backstroke on Monday, clocked 1:55.60, breaking the 15-year-old African record of 1:55.75 set by George du Rand in Rome in 2009.\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1686, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1668, \"end\": 1672, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_African_rand\", \"score\": 0.9999988322817895, \"rank\": 9.545140072099465e-07, \"text\": \"Rand\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_African_rand\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/South_African_rand\"}, {\"begin\": 1676, \"end\": 1680, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"score\": 0.9987947627589779, \"rank\": 0.0012053276834894883, \"text\": \"Rome\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Rome\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Coetze\", \"from\": 1524, \"to\": 1530}, {\"ngram\": \"the 100m backstroke\", \"from\": 1549, \"to\": 1568}, {\"ngram\": \"Monday\", \"from\": 1572, \"to\": 1578}, {\"ngram\": \"clocked 1:55.60\", \"from\": 1580, \"to\": 1595}, {\"ngram\": \"the 15-year-old African record\", \"from\": 1606, \"to\": 1636}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The race was won by former world champion Hubert Kos of Hungary in 1:54.36.\", \"from\": 1688, \"to\": 1763, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1747, \"end\": 1754, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Hungary_national_football_team\", \"score\": 0.988157739900812, \"rank\": 0.011984179716863544, \"text\": \"Hungary\", \"types\": [\"Q476028\", \"Q43229\", \"Q24229398\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resou